          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Wow, CORBA is still around?  That was all the rage in the late 90s - early 00s.  It was a lot of fun to develop for, but man was it slow and bloated.  CORBA was almost entirely replaced in pure java shops first with RMI, and then everybody and their mother jumped headfirst into SOAP and REST/JSON.  None of the latter products had/have CORBA's scope and flexibility, but &quot;good enough&quot; is nearly always enough.<br /><br />BTW, a good book to learn about CORBA is &quot;CORBA for Dummies&quot; (1998).  I always thought that putting &quot;CORBA&quot; and &quot;Dummies&quot; in one sentence was quite the oxymoron, but it really was excellent for learning the basics.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
